A blockchain is a universally accessible database that people contribute to consisting of various data and information. There are numerous types of blockchains such as the ethereum blockchain, or Flow blockchain. Most information on these blockchains cannot be changed. 
Smart contracts are programs that are stored on a blockchain that users can interact with. A smart contract is a transparent way for individuals to see everything going on. They can be tested on the "testnet" to check for success/failures before being deployed on the "mainnet"
The difference between a script and a transaction is simply scripts are used to view information on the Blockchain, costing no money. Transactions changes information on the blockchain and costs different amounts of money depending on the Blockchain its stored on.
